<!-- M-1A4 Powered Suit -->

<ThingDef ParentName="ArmorMachineableBase">
    <defName>Fed_Apparel_M-1A4PoweredSuit</defName>
    <label>M-1A4 Powered Suit</label>
    <description>"The M-1A4 Powered Suit is what makes Mobile Infantry truly mobile. Servo-enhanced strength lets you carry heavy weapons like sidearms and shrug off loads that would break an unassisted human. Integrated jump jets—built right into the armor's frame—launch you across terrain in bounding leaps, letting you cover kilometers rapidly while staying 'on the bounce.' The suit's titanium alloy shell stops everything from small arms to bug mandibles, and full environmental sealing means you can operate anywhere—vacuum, toxic atmospheres, radioactive zones.

Heavy? Yes. Slow? Compared to unarmored troops. But when you're sealed in an M-1A4, you're not just a trooper anymore—you're a walking tank with jump jets. One suited trooper can accomplish what takes a full squad in standard armor. The Federation's enemies learned to fear the distinctive 'steel gorilla' silhouette of powered MI troopers. This is the suit that Heinlein envisioned, the armor that defined powered infantry combat. Service guarantees citizenship—but the M-1A4 guarantees you'll survive to earn it."</description>
    <techLevel>Spacer</techLevel>
    <recipeMaker>
      <researchPrerequisite>Research_FederationArmory</researchPrerequisite>
      <unfinishedThingDef>UnfinishedTechArmor</unfinishedThingDef>
      <skillRequirements>
        <Crafting>4</Crafting>
      </skillRequirements>
      <displayPriority>220</displayPriority>
    </recipeMaker>
    <graphicData>
      <texPath>Things/Items/Apparel/M-1A4PoweredArmor_Male_south</texPath>
